@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - mngdmac/MacOrder
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired MacOrder spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetMacOrder;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListMacOrders using filters compartmentId,\ndisplayName;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateMacOrder\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses CancelMacOrder with required\nvia GetMacOrder or ListMacOrders to DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetMacOrder or\nListMacOrders until OCI reaches DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields commitmentTerm, compartmentId;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeMacOrderCompartment,\nUpdateMacOrder only for mutable fields\ndisplayName, ipRange, orderDescription,\norderSize (+1 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=GetWorkRequest -> GetMacOrder;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest -> GetMacOrder;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nCancelMacOrder/GetMacOrder/ListMacOrders\nconfirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: mngdmac
slug: macorder
kind: MacOrder
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest -> GetMacOrder;
update=GetWorkRequest -> GetMacOrder;
delete=GetWorkRequest ->
CancelMacOrder/GetMacOrder/ListMacOrders
confirm-delete
supported drift: displayName, ipRange,
orderDescription, orderSize (+1 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
commitmentTerm, compartmentId
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_mngdmac_mac_orders filters
compartmentId, displayName; exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING; duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and NEEDS_ATTENTION or FAILED as
terminal failure; DELETING stays terminating and
DELETED is a delete target.
CreateMacOrder returns a MacOrder body plus
opc-work-request-id, while UpdateMacOrder and
CancelMacOrder return work-request headers only.
The runtime follows the service-local
GetWorkRequest helper, recovers the affected
MacOrder OCID from work-request resources, and
rereads GetMacOrder as the authoritative
observed-state source.
Delete maps to CancelMacOrder for the published
Kubernetes contract. The finalizer is released
when rereads confirm DELETED, NotFound, or a
canceled order read-model
(`orderStatus=CANCELED`) after the cancel work
request succeeds.
ChangeMacOrderCompartment remains out of scope;
compartmentId and commitmentTerm stay
replacement-only, while displayName, ipRange,
orderDescription, orderSize, and shape reconcile
in place.
end note
@enduml
